        enDetailContent: "REQUIREMENTS ELICITATION METHODS:\n\nINTERVIEWS:\n• Most common method\n• Individual and group\n• Structured and unstructured\n• Prepare questions in advance\n• Recording and documentation\n\nWORKSHOPS:\n• Intensive collaborative sessions\n• Joint requirements development\n• Business process modeling\n• Rapid consensus building\n\nFOCUS GROUPS:\n• Group discussion with moderator\n• Identifying implicit needs\n• Concept validation\n\nOBSERVATION:\n• Studying users in their natural environment\n• Revealing implicit requirements\n• Discovering gaps between 'said' and 'done'\n\nQUESTIONNAIRES:\n• For large user groups\n• Quantitative data\n• Statistical analysis\n\nHOW TO KNOW COLLECTION IS COMPLETE:\n• Users start repeating themselves\n• New requirements fall outside project scope\n• Models become stable\n• Stakeholders confirm completeness",
