        enDetailContent: "SOFTWARE REQUIREMENTS SPECIFICATION (SRS) — a document describing the expected system behavior. Used in development, testing, and project management.\n\nSRS TEMPLATE:\n\n1. Introduction\n• Document purpose\n• Scope\n• Definitions and acronyms\n• References\n\n2. Overall Description\n• Product vision\n• User classes\n• Operating environment\n• Project constraints\n• Assumptions and dependencies\n\n3. System Features\n• Functional requirements (with unique IDs)\n• Use cases\n\n4. Data Requirements\n• Data models\n• Data dictionary\n\n5. External Interface Requirements\n• User interfaces\n• Hardware interfaces\n• Software interfaces\n• Communication interfaces\n\n6. Quality Attributes\n• Performance\n• Security\n• Reliability\n• Usability\n\n7. Internationalization Requirements\n\nIn agile projects, SRS is often replaced by a set of user stories with acceptance criteria.",
