        enDetailContent: "REQUIREMENTS MODELING helps present knowledge about requirements in visual form and discover gaps.\n\nDATA FLOW DIAGRAM (DFD):\n• Shows data transformation by processes\n• External entities → Processes → Data stores\n• Levels: context (0), decomposition (1, 2...)\n\nSWIMLANE DIAGRAM:\n• Shows business processes with role separation\n• Each 'lane' — responsible party\n• Clearly shows inter-departmental interaction\n\nSTATE TRANSITION DIAGRAM:\n• Shows object lifecycle\n• States → Events → Transitions\n• Useful for objects with complex behavior\n\nDIALOG MAP:\n• Structure of user interface screens\n• Screen transitions\n• Navigation hierarchy\n\nDECISION TABLES:\n• Systematize complex business logic\n• Conditions × Actions = Rules\n\nUML DIAGRAMS:\n• Class, sequence, activity diagrams\n• Industry standard in software",
