        enDetailContent: "DATA REQUIREMENTS describe the structure, relationships, attributes, and processing rules of data in a system.\n\nDATA RELATIONSHIP MODELING:\n• ER diagrams (entity-relationship)\n• Data classes and their attributes\n• Relationships: 1:1, 1:N, M:N\n\nDATA DICTIONARY:\n• Composition (entities, attributes)\n• Definitions and formats\n• Validation rules\n• Data sources\n\nDATA ANALYSIS:\n• What data is created, used, deleted\n• Data lifecycle\n• Storage and archiving requirements\n\nREPORT SPECIFICATIONS:\n• Report purpose\n• Frequency\n• Fields and format\n• Filter criteria\n• Sorting rules\n• Sample output\n\nDASHBOARDS:\n• Key Performance Indicators (KPI)\n• Real-time vs periodic\n• Customizable presentation",
