        enDetailContent: "REQUIREMENTS REUSE — applying previously created requirements in new projects. Accelerates development and improves quality.\n\nTYPES OF REUSE:\n\n1. BY SCOPE:\n• Complete — requirements used without changes\n• Partial — requirements are adapted\n\n2. BY MECHANISM:\n• Copying — direct use\n• Inheritance — child requirements from parent requirements\n• Parameterization — configurable requirements\n\nINFORMATION TYPES FOR REUSE:\n• Individual requirements\n• Features\n• Use cases\n• Rules and constraints\n• Data models\n• Document templates\n\nPOPULAR SCENARIOS:\n• Product lines\n• Reengineering and system replacement\n• Standard modules (authentication, reporting)\n\nREQUIREMENT PATTERNS:\n• Generalized templates for typical requirements\n• Contains: name, problem, solution, examples\n• Accelerates requirement creation\n\nSUCCESS FACTORS:\n• Culture of reuse in the organization\n• Search and cataloging tools\n• Documenting sources\n• Team training",
