        enDetailContent: "REQUIREMENTS ARE THE FOUNDATION for all subsequent development stages.\n\nEFFORT ESTIMATION:\n• Requirements as input for estimation\n• Methods: function points, use case points, story points\n• Uncertainty decreases as requirements are clarified\n\nPROJECT PLANNING:\n• Requirements define scope of work\n• Priorities determine implementation order\n• Dependencies between requirements affect schedule\n\nARCHITECTURE AND DESIGN:\n• Quality requirements influence architectural decisions\n• Functional requirements determine components\n• Constraints limit technology choices\n\nTESTING:\n• Requirements are the basis for test scenarios\n• Traceability: requirement → test → defect\n• Acceptance testing verifies requirement fulfillment\n\nRISK MANAGEMENT:\n• Incomplete or unclear requirements are the main source of risk\n• Early problem identification reduces correction cost\n• Every requirement must be testable\n\nPROJECT SUCCESS:\nA project is considered successful when the product meets requirements within budget and schedule.",
